  "prompt": "What are the best Shahrukh khan movies?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, popularly known as \"SRK\" or \"King Khan,\" has an extensive filmography with many acclaimed movies. While opinions may vary, here are some of SRK's best and most popular films that have been appreciated by audiences and critics alike:\n\n1. **Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge (1995)** - A timeless romantic film that remains one of the most iconic Bollywood movies.\n2. **Kuch Kuch Hota Hai (1998)** - A cult classic featuring a love triangle and unforgettable music.\n3. **My Name Is Khan (2010)** - A compelling drama addressing social issues and featuring a standout performance by SRK.\n4. **Chennai Express (2013)** - A masala entertainer with comedy, action, and romance.\n5. **Kal Ho Naa Ho (2003)** - A heartwarming drama about love and life.\n6. **Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham (2001)** - A family-oriented film with an ensemble cast.\n7. **Devdas (2002)** - An opulent and tragic love story based on the classic novel.\n8. **Swades (2004)** - An inspiring film about social change and self-discovery.\n9. **Dil Se (1998)** - A romantic thriller with memorable music and intense performances.\n10. **Don (2006 & 2011)** - Action-packed crime thrillers where SRK plays a stylish and cunning anti-hero.\n\nThese films represent a mix of genres showcasing Shah Rukh Khan's versatility and impact on Indian cinema.",
